benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios @TC01 cover retrieval with only required accountId.
Empty Response: @TC06 covers case when no custom fields exist.
Query Parameters: Multiple scenarios (@TC02, @TC05, @TC07, @TC08, @TC09, @TC11, @TC13, @TC37, @TC38) test various query parameters including objectType and audit levels.

Error Handling: @TC12, @TC13, @TC14, @TC15, @TC17, @TC18, @TC33, @TC34, @TC35, @TC36 cover invalid accountId formats, non-existent accounts, missing/invalid auth, injection attempts, and invalid parameter formats.
Large Data Handling: @TC11 and @TC30 test large number of custom fields and maximum limits.
Performance & Concurrency: @TC11, @TC25, @TC26, @TC28, @TC29, @TC30, @TC31, @TC32, @TC35, @TC36, @TC40 cover performance under load, concurrency, and edge cases.
Regression & Compatibility: @TC21, @TC22 ensure previous bugs are fixed and backward compatibility.
Service Unavailability & Recovery: @TC16, @TC20, @TC23, @TC24, @TC39 cover system downtime, transient errors, and recovery scenarios.
Security & Injection: @TC17, @TC18, @TC33, @TC35, @TC36 test for SQL injection, XSS, and input validation.
gaps: Pagination: No tests explicitly verify pagination or handling of large datasets beyond count and performance thresholds.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios check for cache headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Authorization: While some auth failure scenarios are covered, explicit tests for permission-based access control are missing.
Detailed audit info levels: While @TC03 and @TC04 cover audit levels, more granular testing of audit content and partial audit info is absent.
Edge cases for input formats: Some edge cases are covered, but specific tests for array or numeric objectType inputs (@TC32) could be expanded.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for pagination handling, including large result sets and page tokens if applicable.
Include tests for cache headers to verify proper caching behavior.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure system handles high request volumes gracefully.
Add permission-based access control tests to verify different user roles and permissions.
Expand audit level testing to include partial or inconsistent audit info scenarios.
Create tests for array or numeric objectType inputs to ensure robust validation.
Include tests for concurrent modifications and race conditions if relevant.
